<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 175 Tons of Eggs Destroyed in South India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-eight million
putrefied eggs (about 175 tons) were buried Saturday in Salem
District of India's southern state of Tamil Nadu, the Press trust
of India (PTI) reported.
</P>
<P>
These rotten eggs were buried in huge pits and the whole
operation lasted nearly four hours, PTI quoted a local official as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The decision to destroye the eggs, which had been kept in cold
storages, was taken by the district collector following reports
that these eggs were supplied for noon meal centers.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of students were hospitalized recently in Salem and
nearby districts following consumption of the eggs which were
found contaminated on analysis.
</P>
<P>
A village chosen earlier for the "burial" was given up after
protests from the local people fearing contamination of ground
water, PTI said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
