<HEADLINE> APPCED Participants On China's Lijiang River (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Lijiang is so clean, with plants along the riverbank,
providing the best evidence of Guilin's success in environmental
protection, according to Pete Hodgson, acting president of the
APPCED Executive Committee and a member of New Zealand House of
Representatives.
</P>
<P>
As the boat approached a famous scenic spot, "Nine Horses
Painting on the Mountain," they could see a cliff a hundred meters
wide decorated with different stones and plants, that seemed a
picture of magic horses.
</P>
<P>
Svetlana Goryacheva, vice-chairperson of the Russian Duma, said
that Guilin deserves applause for its excellent preservation of
this healthy environment in spite of its population density and
booming industry.
</P>
<P>
Edward N. Natapei, speaker of Vanuatu's parliament, praised
China's endeavor and success in environmental protection and cited
them as examples for other countries to follow.
</P>
<P>
President of the National Assembly of Thailand Wan Muhammad Nor
Matha said that the 7th general assembly will be held next year in
Chiangmai, Thailand, and that Li Peng, Chairman of the Standing
Committee of China's National People's Congress, has promised that
China will offer its support. He said he hopes that the Chiangmai
Assembly will be a success and help promote environmental
protection legislation of APPCED's members so as to preserve the
living environment of the mankind.
</P>
<P>
The 64-km cruise lasted four and half hours. Qu Geping, the
best-known Chinese environmental protection specialist and
president of this year's assembly, said, "The expression
that 'Guilin's landscape is the best under the heaven' is
absolutely true both historically and in reality. Guilin is an
epitome of improved environmental protection in China and shows
our determination to leave a better world for the next
generation." 
</P>
</TEXT>
