<HEADLINE> APPCED Participants On China's Lijiang River (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The mountains and rivers of the
city of Guilin have an appeal for foreign representatives who are
here for the 6th General Assembly of the Asia-Pacific
Parliamentarians' Conference on Environment and Development
(APPCED).
</P>
<P>
Leaning against the railing of the boat "Panorama" that took
President Bill Clinton on a cruise on Guilin's Lijiang River, Jack
Fritz, speaker of Micronesia's parliament, said today that he
appreciated the crystal-clear water and green mountains.
</P>
<P>
For most representatives, this is their first visit to China,
and they say that it is well worthwhile to discuss environmental
protection and see the mountains and rivers of Guilin.
</P>
<P>
Fritz says that what he experienced this time was totally
different from some news reports he had came across before, and
that Guilin has green trees and grass everywhere, and the Lijiang
is as clear as river in Micronesia, and the people are friendly.
</P>
<P>
This morning, nearly 100 APPCED participants arrived at the
Zhujiang dock and began their cruise on the Lijiang River on what
is called "a painted corridor of mountains and rivers."
</P>
</TEXT>
