<HEADLINE> Sino-Saudi Joint Press Communique (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The two sides worry about the stalemate in the Mideast peace
process and reiterate the importance of the already established
principles, in particular the principle of "land for peace" and
relevant resolutions of the U.N. Security Council.
</P>
<P>
The two emphasize that the relevant parties must abide by their
commitment to signed agreements and underline the importance of
the Jerusalem issue and the necessity to avoid any one-sided
action that may affect the outcome of negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The two sides appeal to the international community to take
prompt action for a thorough, just and lasting peace in the Middle
East.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, both sides appeal to Syria and Israel to resume
negotiations and that Resolution No. 426 of the U.N. Security
Council on Lebanon be effectively implemented.
</P>
<P>
The two sides deeply worry about the deadlock in Iraqi weapons
inspections and ask Iraq to resume cooperating with the UN Special
Commission on the basis of UN Resolution No.1194 of the Security
Council. They demand that Iraq completely and thoroughly implement
all the relevant UN resolutions and emphasize the necessity of
implementing UN Security Council resolutions on meeting the
humanitarian needs of the Iraqi people. The two sides underline
the importance of respecting the independence, sovereignty and
territorial integration of Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The two countries condemn terrorist activities of any kind,
from any side, and emphasize their willingness to step up
anti-terrorist efforts between the two countries, as well as the
importance of international cooperation for the accomplishment of
this goal.
</P>
</TEXT>
