<HEADLINE> Sino-Saudi Arabian Joint Press Communique (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Crown Prince Abdullah Ibn abdul
Aziz Al Saud, deputy prime minister of Saudi Arabia and head of
the National Guard, left here today on a continuation of his China
visit to Xian and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The two countries issued a joint press communique on the Crown
Prince's visit, as follows:
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of Zhu Rongji, Premier of the People's
Republic of China, Crown Prince Abdullah Ibn abdul Aziz Al Saud,
deputy prime-minister and head of the National Guard of Saudi
Arabia, pays an official visit to China from October 14 to 21, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin met with Crown Prince
Abdullah. Premier Zhu Rongji held talks with Crown Prince
Abdullah. The two sides exchanged views and reached a consensus on
bilateral ties, and other regional and global issues of common
concern in a cordial and friendly atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan, Minister of the State
Economic and Trade Commission Sheng Huaren, and Vice-minister of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Sun Guangxiang also held
discussions with Saudi officials.
</P>
<P>
The two countries are satisfied with the noticeable progress
that have been scored since they forged diplomatic ties eight
years ago and underline that they are willing to raise bilateral
cooperation in political and economic fields to a new strategic
level.
</P>
</TEXT>
