<HEADLINE> Sino-Saudi Joint Press Communique (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Saudi side emphasizes the principles issued in a memorandum
of understanding on establishing diplomatic relations and a joint
communique between the two governments that the People's Republic
of China is the sole legal government representing the whole
Chinese people, and Taiwan is an inseparable part of the Chinese
territory, and the Chinese side expressed its appreciations for
this.
</P>
<P>
The two sides are pleased to see the growth trend in bilateral
trade, as well as the opportunities and potential for bilateral
economic cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agree to continue efforts to promote trade
exchanges, and encourage exports. The two sides signed a
memorandum of understanding on four working groups in a bilateral
economic and trade committee as a forum on cooperation in trade,
oil and mineral resources, investment, and technology.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agree to encourage enterpreneurs of the two
countries to establish a joint council for expanding trade and
investment.
</P>
<P>
Both sides underline the importance of the stability of oil
market on the global economy. Saudi Arabia, as a safe and reliable
supplier of the global oil market, plays an eminent role in
ensuring this stability. The Chinese praise the part played by the
Saudi Arabia, and they are willing to increase their cooperative
ties in trade and investment in the petroleum field.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Both sides note that the China visit by Crown Prince
Abdullah Ibn abdul Aziz Al Saud has yielded good results. and They
have reached consensus that bilateral high-level contacts will be
maintained and coordination and cooperation between the two
countries will be enhanced.  
</P>
</TEXT>
