<DOCNO> XIE19981018.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambian Farmers Urge Better Fertilizer Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The Zambia National Farmers
Union (ZNFU) proposed here Saturday to set up a fertilizer
management system.
</P>
<P>
ZNFU President Ajay Vashee made the proposal in a speech read
on his behalf by ZNFU acting Executive Director Songowayo Zyambo
at a farmers' crusade here.
</P>
<P>
The steering committee should be comprised of government,
private fertilizer companies, farmers and other relevant
institutions, he said.
</P>
<P>
It should distribute fertilizer when there is shortfall in
fertilizer, to ensure a sustainable development of the sector.
</P>
<P>
For 1994-1995 and 1995-1996 seasons, a lot of fertilizer was
issued on credit but a large portion of this remained uncollected
because of poor repayment by both farmers and traders, he said.
</P>
<P>
Vashee attributed the loss to lack of a system to punish
defaulting farmers and traders, a system he said will strengthen
and make the whole fertilizer exercise meaningful.
</P>
<P>
On the same occasion, Agriculture Deputy Minister Yotam
Ngulube said the government is aware of the presence of
privately-procured fertilizer in the country.
</P>
<P>
The government is making arrangements to make the fertilizer
available to farmers on credit basis, he said.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated the government's commitment to the development
of the agriculture sector and said that agriculture is the only
key to Zambia's ailing economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
