<HEADLINE> Armed Groups Attack Serbian Police in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, October 18 (Xinhua) -- The Kosovo ethnic Albanian
armed men attacked several Serbian police checkpoints in the
crisis-hit province Saturday, killing three Serb policemen, the
Yugoslav news agency Tanjug reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The three policemen were shot dead at the Orlate village near
the Pristina-Malisevo road. Two other policemen were seriously
injured.
</P>
<P>
Another armed group, on the same day, sprayed bullets at a
police car in the Magur district, injuring two policemen.
</P>
<P>
A Serbian police checkpoint at Komorane, about 20 kilometers
away from the provincial capital of Pristina, was also under fire
several time on Saturday night. But no casualty was reported.
</P>
<P>
The Serbian police and the Yugoslav army said that they were
pulling out of western Kosovo's battlefields under an agreement
struck by Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic and U.S. envoy
Richard Holbrooke.
</P>
<P>
However, the Kosovo ethnic Albanian armed groups, who fought
for the independence of the province, have constantly attacked the
Serbian police since the signing of the agreement. 
</P>
