<HEADLINE> Turkey, Syria to Hold Talks to Ease Tensions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail
Cem has said that Turkish and Syrian high-ranking officials plan
to hold security talks in the coming days in a bid to ease
tensions between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Cem told the semi-official Anatolia News Agency late Saturday
night that the Turkish-Syrian talks would take place, but gave no
fixed place and time.
</P>
