<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Koo Chen-fu Holds Press Party for His Visit to Mainland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Koo Chen-fu, chairman of the
Taiwan-based Straits Exchange Foundation (SEF), held a press party
here this evening where he frequently used the word "very" to
describe his current visit to the Chinese mainland.
</P>
<P>
He described his meeting with Jiang Zemin, general secretary of
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), as
proceeded in an atmosphere of "very cordial" where they held "free
conservation."
</P>
<P>
On the consensus reached between Koo and Wang Daohan, president
of the Association for Relations Across Taiwan Straits (ARATS),
and Wang's planned visit to Taiwan, he said that he felt "very"
gratified.
</P>
<P>
Talking about his visit to the mainland, Koo said that he was
"very" grateful for the considerate reception arrangements made by
ARATS.
</P>
<P>
He said, "We have come to the mainland with good-will and we
will return to Taiwan with friendship."
</P>
<P>
Koo, the leader of the Taiwan authorized non-governmental
organization, said that the two sides across the Straits can have
"constructive dialogue" including dialogues on political, economic
and practical issues.
</P>
<P>
He said that through this meeting, both sides have come to
realize the importance of "constructive dialogue" and the
necessity of continuing the dialogue and raising its level, adding
that the two sides have taken a first and significant step.
</P>
<P>
He said that the significance of the Wang-Koo meeting can be
seen in the four-point consensus reached by the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Koo added that Jiang Zemin and Qian Qichen think this consensus
is valuable.
</P>
<P>
Koo said that during his visit to the mainland he learned about
the economic reforms and opening up here over the past two decades.
</P>
<P>
He noted that people's lives on the two sides of the straits
are much better than in the past, and both sides should value this
achievement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
