<HEADLINE> Romania to Fully Develop Ties With China: Senate Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Romania and China should make
joint efforts in further developing the traditional friendly
relations between the two countries, Romanian Senate Chairman
Petre Roman said this weekend.
</P>
<P>
When answering written questions from Xinhua, Roman noted that
through his visit to China last month, he has had a deeper
understanding of the real long-term strategic partnership between
Romania and China.
</P>
<P>
The two countries should fully strengthen their cooperation in
all fields, especially in the area of economic and trade, Roman
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that there are broad prospects for economic and trade
cooperation between Romania and China, adding that the current
cooperation is far from enough. It is possible for the two nations
to boost their annual trade to 1 billion U.S. dollars, he said.
</P>
<P>
Roman also urged the two countries to expand mutually
beneficial cooperation in the areas of industries and
investment. Romanian design institutes and experts can participate
in investment programs in China, while China can invest in
Romania's construction programs in Constansta Harbor.
</P>
<P>
Roman expressed his belief that the forthcoming meeting of the
Romanian-Chinese Economic and Trade Cooperation Committee in
Beijing will speed up the implementation of those programs still
on the waiting list.
</P>
<P>
He said he has instructed Industry and Trade Minister Radu
Berceanu, who will lead a Romanian delegation to the meeting, to
make full preparations for the discussion with China on seeking
ways to improve bilateral economic and trade cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
