<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-18 15:22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian Students Stage Rally Against Guardians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 18 (Xinhua) -- A group of Iranian university
students from the left-wing factions staged a rally here Sunday
afternoon against the policy of the conservative Guardians Council.
</P>
<P>
The official news agency IRNA said the students announced their
opposition to the policy of the Guardians Council to screen
qualifications of candidates for elections in the country.
</P>
<P>
Heshmatollah Tabarzadi, secretary general of the Islamic Union
of the Students and Graduates, criticized the council at the
rally for rejecting a number of nominees for the Experts Assembly
election on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The report did not give the number of students attending the
rally, but said that the protest rally was authorized by the
Interior Ministry and was guarded by anti-riot police.
</P>
<P>
During the rally, about 100 students from opposition groups
chanted slogans against the organizers of the rally, IRNA said,
but no clash was reported.
</P>
<P>
The rally was organized after at least three famous candidates
of the left and moderate factions withdrew from the election
campaigns for the Experts Assembly in a protest to the Guardians
Council's screening policy.
</P>
<P>
The conservative-dominated council was accused by the factions
supporting President Mohammad Khatami of taking side while
reviewing the qualifications of applicants for the Experts
Assembly, which determines the country's supreme leader.
</P>
<P>
The council has approved 168 candidates out of 396 to run
for the 86-seat Experts Assembly, which is also empowered to
dismiss the leader according to the constitution.
</P>
<P>
However, the conservative factions rejected the charges against
the Guardians Council, but accused the leftists and moderates of
trying to undermine the election.
</P>
<P>
The Experts Assembly was formed in 1983 under the order of late
Iranian supreme leader Ayatollah Musavi Khomeini to elect his
successor. It serves in each term of eight years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
