<HEADLINE> NBA Veterans Beat Chinese National Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 18 (Xinhua) -- The XNBA team, coached by
legend Oscar Robertson, trounced Chinese men's national
basketball team 86-73 here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The NBA veterans, including six-time NBA champion winner
Kareem Abdul-Jabbar, raced to a 14-7 lead five minutes into
action and increased the lead to 33-17 eight minutes before the
interval.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese national team, which won the first match of the
four-game series 98-96 on Friday, fought back strongly with three
three-pointers from Zhang Jinsong and Li Nan, narrowing the
margin to 38-34 with 40 seconds remaining in the first half.
</P>
<P>
But the Chinese never came closer than that and was
overwhelmed after the break, having no way to score before the
solid defence of the former NBA greats.
</P>
<P>
"The players felt embarrassed after the defeat in the first
match," said Robertson. "We have expected the results."
</P>
<P>
Wang Fei, head coach of the Chinese side, said the defeat was
even more beneficial than the victory in the first match.
</P>
<P>
"They are the former NBA players, they are more experienced,
so we learned a lot from them," Wang said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will travel to Hefei, An'hui province, to play
their third match on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
