<HEADLINE> Local Election Begins in Hungary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Hungarians cast ballots on
Sunday to elect local government officials.
</P>
<P>
Over 8 million registered voters are expected to vote to elect
41,000 local officials on Sunday, at 10,527 polling stations in
3,153 villages and towns all over the country.
</P>
<P>
A total 101,000 candidates contested the 41,000 posts.
</P>
<P>
The candidate who wins the most votes will get the post in the
one-round-only election.
</P>
<P>
All main political parties had taken part in the campaign, with
30 million copies of campaigning materials printed.
</P>
<P>
The election results will be released on Monday night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
