<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh
Chok Tong Sunday urged Singaporeans to take an active part in
sports so as to enhance physical and mental fitness for
weathering pressures and difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the launch of the Sports for Life Employee Fitness
Programme, Goh Chok Tong attached importance of a physically and
mentally fit nation that is able to withstand pressures.
</P>
