<HEADLINE> China to Improve Investment Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese trade official
said here today that the country is trying its best to improve the
investment environment and help overseas investors solve practical
problems.
</P>
<P>
Sun Guangxiang, vice minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation, made the remarks at the ongoing central-west
China-overseas trade fair attended by more than 2,000 business
people from over 50 countries and regions from Asia, America and
Europe.
</P>
<P>
According to Sun, China is now reinforcing legislation related
to overseas investment to ensure benefits to overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
The country is simplifying the formalities for approval of
overseas investment as well as making the procedure open and
transparent, Sun said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the country will also conduct annual checks
of overseas-funded enterprises to make sure they are enjoying
proper national treatment.
</P>
<P>
Liu Mingkang, vice governor the People's Bank of China, also
reported to the trade fair that China's financial sector is
maintaining growth momentum amid the Asian financial crisis,
thanks to a series of policies implemented since 1993. 
</P>
