<DOCNO> XIE19981018.0060 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Reservoir in South China Goes into Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 18 (Xinhua) -- A reservoir with a storage
capacity of 330 million cubic meters on the Moyangjiang River in
South China's Guangdong Province began retaining water today, and
is expected to begin generating electricity by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Located in the city of Yangjiang, the Dahe reservoir is
expected to help prevent the lower reaches of the river from
major flooding.
</P>
<P>
Since 1950, large floods have occurred every four to five years on
the Moyangjiang River, causing nearly 100 million yuan in economic
losses each time.
</P>
<P>
Costing more than 600 million yuan, the multi-functional
reservoir controls a drainage area of 438 square kilometers and
has an installed capacity of 30,000 kw. 
</P>
</TEXT>
