<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Vows to Protect Environment, Cultural Heritage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, October 18 (Xinhua) -- China vowed today that it will
strengthen cooperation with other countries, shoulder the
responsibility of protecting the region's environment and cultural
heritage, and make its due contribution to turning the
Asia-Pacific region into a more beautiful, cleaner and more
vigorous region.
</P>
<P>
Qu Geping, head of the Chinese delegation to the 6th General
Assembly of the Asia-Pacific Parliamentarians Conference on
Environment and Development (APPCED) held here in Guilin, made these
remarks today in announcing a state report concerning tourism and
environmental protection in China.
</P>
<P>
Delegations from other countries also presented their state
reports during the congress this morning.
</P>
<P>
Qu noted that the Chinese government is actively attending to
the coordinated development of tourism and environmental
protection, and has taken measures to protect the tourism
environment and resources, which in turn has brought sound
development to the tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
Qu said that in the next century, trans-regional and
trans-border tourism will boom and environmental protection will
witness further development. In this regard, Qu noted, it is high
time and necessary that cooperative relations in tourism
and environmental protection be established in the Asian-Pacific
region.
</P>
<P>
With varied natural landscapes and historic and cultural
traditions, China's tourism resources are among the most abundant
in the world, Qu said, pointing out that tourism environment
will determine the survival and development of tourism.
</P>
<P>
That's why China has paid great attention to protecting the
tourism environment and has worked to balance economic returns
with social and environmental effects, Qu stressed.
</P>
<P>
He said China is taking the following major steps: formulating
a series of laws and regulations on environmental protection and
protection of the tourism environment and resources according to
law; carrying on with cross-century green project plans to improve
the environment; designating tourism resources as under state
protection and taking specific measures to ensure that protection;
selecting pilot cities and citing them as Model
Environmentally Friendly Cities and National Hygienic Cities with
a view to improving the environment of tourism cities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
