<HEADLINE> CAS to Step Up Ecological, Environmental Study of Yangtze </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, October 18 (Xinhua) -- The China Academy of Sciences
(CAS) announced today that its subordinate institutions along the
Yangtze River Basin will cooperate in research into the ecological
and environmental conditions along this largest river in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The research is aimed at rebuilding the ecology and
environment of the area.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made by CAS's vice president Chen Yiyu at
the closing of a four-day symposium on the causes of and solutions
to flooding in the Yangtze River area, which was attended by some
100 CAS scientists.
</P>
<P>
The participants agreed that economic development and increased
human activities have led to the gradual worsening of
ecological and environmental conditions in the area.
</P>
<P>
There are over 20 CAS subsidiaries in the Yangtze River Basin
including five state-level laboratories and 21 monitoring
stations. With this decision of the CAS, they will join hands in
launching a series of research programs dedicated to ecological
and environmental rebuilding efforts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
