<HEADLINE> China Suffers 2-3 Defeat at Asian Youth Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 18 (Xinhua) -- China suffered a 2-3 defeat on
the opening day of the under-19 Asian Youth Football Championship
at Chiang Mai on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team played to a goalless draw after the first
half against South Korea. Li Yi opened the scoring at the 50th
minute but only one minute later Kim Eun Jung levelled the score
at 1-1.
</P>
<P>
Kim Eun Jung put the South Korean team 2-1 ahead at the 68th
minute. Lee Dong Gook also scored at the 75th minute to
consolidate the lead for the South Korean team.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team fought hard and was awarded a goal at the
85th minute through Shang Yi. But they failed to find an
equalizer before the final whistle.
</P>
<P>
In a match played later on Sunday, Qatar edged Iraq 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Ten teams are participating in the championship which is also
the qualifying tournament for the under-20 World Championship to
be played in Nigeria next year.
</P>
<P>
The top three teams of the championship will qualify for the
World Championship. 
