<HEADLINE> Sichuan Urged to Speed Up Water, Soil Conservation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Sichuan Province has been urged
to improve its ecological environment and guarantee flood-control
safety on the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River and
the long-term safety of the Three Gorges Project.
</P>
<P>
A law-enforcement inspection team, led by Buhe, vice-chairman
of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC),
made the request to the government of Sichuan here today when the
team completed its inspection of water and soil conservation in
the province.
</P>
<P>
Team members recognized the efforts Sichuan has made towards
water and soil conservation, and also pointed out that the
cultivation of hillside land was the main cause of soil erosion on
the upper reaches of the Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
Southwest China's Sichuan Province, watered by the upper
reaches of Yangtze, is one of the most important agricultural
provinces in China.
</P>
<P>
Jing Zhengshu, deputy governor of Sichuan, pledged that the
province will find solutions to the problems raised by the
inspection team.
</P>
<P>
Jing said Sichuan will increase investment in controlling soil
erosion over a wider area, and suggested that a compensation fund
be set up for eco-construction on the upper reaches of the Yangtze
to accelerate water and soil conservation in the region with
support from the entire country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
