<HEADLINE> Nepali Climber Breaks Mount Qomolangma Speed Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Kaji Sherpa of Nepal
shattered an eight-year-old record for the fastest time to reach
the summit of Mount Qomolangma, the world's tallest mountain,
according to local reports.
</P>
<P>
Kaji reached the summit after an exhausting all night climb
without the use of oxygen. He reached the summit at 12:24 p.m.
on Saturday, the Nepal Television and state-radio announced.
</P>
<P>
His time of 20 hours and 24 minutes beat the record set eight
years ago by Frenchman marc Batard who took 22 hours 29 minutes.
</P>
