<HEADLINE> Frontier Trade Fair Attracts Southeast Asian Businesses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, October 18 (Xinhua) -- The Lancangjiang-Mekong
Sub-regional Economic Cooperation Xishuangbanna Frontier Trade
Fair opened today in the border city of Jinghong in southwest
China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
Some 276 enterprises from at home and abroad gathered at
Jinghong, capital city of Xishuangbanna Dai Autonomous Prefecture,
to attend the 10-day trade fair.
</P>
<P>
Thailand, Laos, and Myanmar all have delegations at the fair,
along with business people from Malaysia, Japan, and China's Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region, Macao, and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The Lancangjiang (known as the Mekong River outside China)-Mekong
sub-region is currently hot among international investors.
</P>
<P>
Xishuangbanna has six roads linking it with contiguous areas of
Laos and Myanmar. Four of these roads link up with others to
Thailand, and a one-day trip on the Lancangjiang River will take
people to Thailand from the port of Jinghong.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen provinces and municipalities have set up 114 exhibit
stands to display their quality products.
</P>
<P>
The Xishuangbanna Frontier Trade Fair was first held last year
with a total trade volume of 184 million yuan (22.2 million U.S.
dollars). The fair is considered an important means of
cooperation for the Lancangjiang-Mekong sub-region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
