<HEADLINE> People's Daily Hails Opening of Unions' Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 18 (Xinhua) -- People's Daily, the mouthpiece
of the ruling Communist Party of China (CPC), Monday issues an
editorial to hail the opening of the Thirteenth National Congress
of All-China Federation of Trade Unions.
</P>
<P>
The editorial terms the congress an important event for the
political life of workers of all nationalities in the country as
it is held shortly after the closing of the Third Plenary Session
of the Fifteenth CPC Central Committee and the two-decade old
reform has entered into a crucial stage.
</P>
<P>
It stresses the working class have made eternal contributions
to the reform, opening and modernization drive with their lofty
sense of responsibility as the master of the country and the
spirit of working hard to start an undertaking.
</P>
<P>
The history of nearly one century indicates that the Chinese
working class is indeed the representative of the advanced
productivity, the leading class of the country and the back-bone
force to push forward the social progress, the editorial says.
</P>
<P>
The paper speaks highly of what trade unions of all levels have
achieved since the 12th national congress of trade unions, calling
the unions a bridge between the party and the massive workers, an
important social pillar of the State regime, and the
representative of the interests of trade union members and all
kinds of employees in the country.
</P>
<P>
The editorial urges the working class to unite and work hard to
carry out the current state enterprise reform, fulfil all tasks
proposed by CPC and the government, and to compete with each other
to make greater contribution to the development of national
economy.
</P>
<P>
The trade unions must accept the leadership of the Party
conscientiously and work independently in line with the law and
the constitution of the All-China Federation of Trade Unions, the
paper says, noting that the unions have to keep in mind the
general situation of the Party and national work as well as the
interests of the Chinese people. 
