<HEADLINE> Inflation Down, Food Prices Surge in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 18 (Xinhua) -- The annual rate of inflation
in India fell by 0.47 percent to 8.22 percent for the week ending
October 3 compared with 8.69 percent a week earlier, according to
official figures published here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
But prices of food articles, especially vegetables, surged
sharply with the index for all commodities (base: 1981-82=100)
registered a 0.4 percent increase to 357.9 in the week compared
with 356.6 in the previous week.
</P>
<P>
In the current week, marked by the sharp increase in the prices
of onions, index of vegetables shot up by 11.4 percent from last
week.
</P>
<P>
The rate of inflation based on the final index for the week
ending August 8 stood at 8.1 percent compared with 7.9 percent on
the provisional index while final index for all commodities for
the week stood at 352.3 as against 351.0 on the provisional index.
</P>
<P>
Though the inflation is still within the manageable limit,
inflation measured on the consumer price index for industrial
workers, a better indicator of the rate of increase in prices, is
at the astronomical 15.4 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
