<HEADLINE> Sixth APPCED General Assembly Closes in Guilin (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, October 18 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth General Assembly of
the Asia-Pacific Parliamentarians' Conference on Environment and
Development (APPCED) closed today in the scenic city
of Guilin, southwest China.
</P>
<P>
Participants signed the "Guilin Declaration" regarding
environmental protection and sustainable tourism, and reached a
series of consensus on challenges and strategic actions in this
regard.
</P>
<P>
The Declaration points out that countries in the Asia-Pacific
region share long-term common goals and broad common interests in
regard to rationally developing resources and strengthening
ecological and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The principles of sustainable development and international
cooperation in the field of environment and development adopted at
the 1992 United Nations Conference on Environment and Development
provide guidance for the pursuit of sustainable development in the
Asia-Pacific region, the Declaration says.
</P>
<P>
It is particularly important that the developed countries take
practical steps and measures to fulfill their stated commitment to
provide new and additional financial resources to developing
countries and to facilitate the transfer of environmentally sound
technologies on favorable terms, it adds.
</P>
<P>
"The rich natural resources and the diverse cultural heritage
of the Asia-Pacific region are treasures of our citizens and
future generations.
</P>
<P>
"We are worried and concerned about environmental damage in the
context of forest habitats, soil erosion and degradation,
biodiversity, water and marine pollution and declining air
quality," the Declaration says.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981018.0097 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sixth APPCED General Assembly Closes in Guilin (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Declaration says that sustainable tourism and environmental
protection go hand in hand and that a sound legal framework is an
important factor in ensuring the reasonable utilization of natural
resources.
</P>
<P>
It appeals to and urges the parliaments and governments of all
countries in the Asia-Pacific region to promote sustainable
development through bilateral and multilateral cooperation in the
international community.
</P>
<P>
The governments are asked to actively formulate and implement
policies and strategies for the development of sustainable
tourism, strengthen the protection of their natural resources,
environment and cultural heritage by laying a solid foundation for
sustainable tourism and strengthening relevant legislation and
enforcement provisions concerning the effective protection of
natural resources, the environment and cultural heritage.
</P>
<P>
The Declaration also urges the governments to promote public
awareness and educational activities related to natural resources
and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The tourism business operators are asked by the Declaration to
consider models of tourism that emphasize environmental
protection.
</P>
</TEXT>
