<HEADLINE> African Women's Football Championship Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 18 (Xinhua) -- The inaugural African Women's
Football Championship opened here on Sunday with the host team
trouncing Morocco 8-0 and Democratic Congo Republic beating Egypt
4-1 on the opening day.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian team dominated the match from the very beginning
with Nkiru Okosieme opening the scoring at the 17th minute.
Patience Avre made it 2-0 for the host team at the 30th minute
and Okosieme stroke again just before the interval.
</P>
<P>
The second half saw the host team enjoy greater advantage.
Rita Nwadike hit twice while captain Omagbemi, Mercy Akide and
Avre each scored once to seal up the 8-0 victory for the host
team.
</P>
<P>
Later on Sunday, South Africa will take on Ghana, Mozambique
clashes with Cameroon in Lagos.
</P>
<P>
Altogether eight teams are participating in the championship.
Nigeria, together with Morocco, Democratic Congo Republic and
Egypt are in Group A, South Africa, Mozambique, Ghana and
Cameroon are in Group B.
</P>
<P>
The top two finishers of the championship will represent Africa
 to take part in the Women's World Cup to be held in the United
States in 1999. 
</P>
