<HEADLINE> UAE Cuts Interest Rates to Stimulate Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, October 18 (Xinhua) -- The central bank of the
United Arab Emirates (UAE) has decided to cut interest rates on
inter-bank lending, deposits and loans as of October 18.
</P>
<P>
The UAE daily Al-Ithad Sunday quoted informed sources as saying
that the move came after the U.S. Federal Reserve Board further
lowered interest rates by a quarter of a percentage point Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the UAE central bank decision, interest rates for
one-month, three-month and six months deposits are all cut by
one-quarter percentage point while one-year interest rate was
lowered from 4.8125 percent to 4.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The lower cost in borrowing money stemming from the interest
cuts will encourage the enterprises to apply for more loans and
expand investment, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
And reduced interest rates on deposits will dampen the
enthusiasm of personal saving and boost consumption to some
extent, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the national economy will be stimulated, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said that the interest cut decision has received
wide welcome among banks, which believe that the step will boost
investment and consumption.
</P>
<P>
The sources speculated that the U.S. Federal Reserve will
further cut interest rates by the end of this year in an effort to
keep the U.S. economy afloat at a time of global economic
turmoil. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
