<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Urges Early Cross-Straits Political Talks (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If the Taiwan side has any misgivings about political talks and
procedural talks, SEF and ARATS may increase contacts and
exchanges and have dialogues first, exchanging views on various
issues of common concern or each other's concern with regard to
the cross-strait relations, including political issues, Qian
stressed, adding that they may exchange views on all issues that
are conducive to peaceful reunification and the development of the
cross-strait relations.
</P>
<P>
He said "one China" principle is the basis for maintaining
stability and developing cross-strait relations and is also
recognized by various countries in the world.
</P>
<P>
"We are not in favor of all statements and actions about 'two
Chinas' or 'one China, one Taiwan'. Nor will we tolerate Taiwan to
be ceded," Qian stressed.
</P>
<P>
Qian said the Taiwan side often complains its room of
international existence has been constrained. In fact, it is the
inevitable outcome of the development of the objective situation.
</P>
<P>
Now 126 counties has so far established diplomatic ties with
the People's Republic of China, while only over 20 countries have
maintained relations with Taiwan, and this trend is still
developing, Qian said.
</P>
<P>
"I hope Taiwan authorities can objectively view the mainland of
the motherland, courageously face the international situation,
take the country and national interests into real account and take
substantial steps to promote the development of the cross-strait
relations and realize the peaceful reunification at an early
date," said Qian.  
</P>
</TEXT>
