<HEADLINE> Rios Wins Singapore Open Tennis Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Chile's Marcelo Rios
defeated Australian Mark Woodforde 6-4, 6-2 in the final to win
the Singapore Open tennis tournament here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Woodforde, 33, could never put Rios in serious trouble in the
final despite his effort to slow down the pace of the match and
to wait his opponent to make mistakes.
</P>
<P>
Rios broke Woodforde's service once in the first set and
opened up the second set breaking Woodforde's opening serving
game.
</P>
<P>
The Australian responded by breaking back in the fourth game
but could not stop Rios taking the following games to wrap the
victory for his seventh title this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
