<HEADLINE> Addis Varsity Selected as Entomology Study Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 18 (Xinhua) -- The Addis Ababa University
has been selected as Post-graduate Entomology Study Center for
East Africa, The Ethiopian Herald reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
This was made at a ceremony launching the post-graduate
educational program in insect science for east African sub-region
in the Biology Department of the Addis Ababa University Thursday,
by university president Mogese Ashenafi.
</P>
<P>
On the occasion, Mogese said the selection of the university
as Post-graduate Entomology Study Center for East Africa comes as
an additional recognition for the institution's excellence.
</P>
<P>
This makes Ethiopia the third country in Africa after Zimbabwe
and Ghana to be the center of post-graduate insect science study
or entomology, said Mogese.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the center will play a major role in fighting
diseases caused to millions of people by insects which are also
destroying huge quantities of grains in the fields and in
storages.
</P>
<P>
Scholars from different universities of various African
countries attended the launching ceremony, said the report.
</P>
