<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Lists Tasks for Agricultural, Rural Development (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 18 (Xinhua) -- China has listed the major
tasks for agriculture and rural work between now and 2010 to
ensure the sustained development of agriculture and other rural
undertakings, according to a decision of the ruling Communist
Party of China (CPC) released here today.
</P>
<P>
The "Decision of the CPC Central Committee on Several Major
Issues in Agriculture and Rural Work" was adopted at the Third
Plenum of the 15th CPC Central Committee on October 14, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The tasks are as follows:
</P>
<P>
-- Stabilize the system of combining unified and separated
operations, with the household contract responsibility system as
the basis.
</P>
<P>
This conforms with both the traditional farming which mainly
relies on manual labor and the modern farming which uses advanced
science and technology and production methods.
</P>
<P>
The key to this is the land contract system. This is the
cornerstone of the Party's rural policies and should never change.
</P>
<P>
China's policy is to renew the land contract system for another
30 years, draft laws and decrees to ensure the long-term stability
of land contract relations and grant long-term land-use rights to
farmers.
</P>
<P>
-- The reforms of the farm produce distribution system should
be continued and the management of the farm produce market system
should be improved.
</P>
<P>
Grain has a strategic importance in the national economy and in
people's life. The reforms of the distribution system have the
purpose of self-sufficiency in grain on the domestic market,
protecting farmers' enthusiasm, and a steady increase in grain
production.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981018.0130 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Lists Tasks for Agricultural, Rural Development (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Grain purchasing market needs to be well managed to make sure
that the state controls the source of grain; retail grain markets
remain open and multi-channel operations and a competitive
mechanism formed so as to meet the diversified demands of the
market.
</P>
<P>
The state will build a grain risk fund, grain reserve, and
system of purchasing grain at a protective price to regulate the
grain market and protect the interests of both farmers and
consumers.
</P>
<P>
-- Accelerate agricultural capital projects construction
centered on water conservation and improve the farming environment.
</P>
<P>
The most urgent task at the moment is increasing input in water
conservation efforts and harnessing the major rivers and lakes
like the Yangtze and Yellow rivers to increase their ability to
control floods.
</P>
<P>
An effort will be made to complete construction of high quality
embankments along major rivers and lakes, and reinforce
reservoirs; and clear away silt to restore the flood-control
ability.
</P>
<P>
Construction work on the Three Gorges and Xiaolangdi projects
should be accelerated to increase the ability to regulate
floodwaters.
</P>
<P>
-- Optimizing agriculture and the rural economic structure
through science and technology.
</P>
<P>
A revolution in agricultural science and technology requires
the application of bio-engineering and information and other high
and new technologies and the use of farm machinery, chemical
fertilizers, and plastic film for a fundamental change in
agricultural science, technology and productive forces.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981018.0131 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Lists Tasks for Agricultural, Rural Development (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- Intensify the effort to ensure an affluent life for the
farmers and speed up the pace of helping the needy in rural China.
</P>
<P>
An affluent life means that farmers have adequate food and
clothing and means of subsistence, improved living environment,
good health, and better education. This means increasing incomes
and reducing burdens of the farmers, a basic requisite to this
end, and it is also important to developing the rural market and
increasing domestic demand.
</P>
<P>
Aid-the-needy spending from various channels will be increased
by a big margin and efforts should be made to help resettle the
small number of people who live in areas with extremely difficult
conditions.
</P>
<P>
-- Build democratic legal system at the grass-roots
level. Efforts should be made to Promote democratic elections,
decisionmaking, management, and supervision at the village level.
</P>
<P>
The building of democracy at the township level is an important
part of grass-roots democracy. The direct election of deputies to
the People's Congress at the township level will be adhered and
improved. Expanding democracy at the grass-roots level should be
under the Party's leadership and should proceed in an orderly
manner. The leading role of Party organizations at the village and
township levels should be brought into full play.
</P>
<P>
-- Promote socialist cultural and ethic progress in rural
China. There must be education on patriotism, collectivism,
socialism, the Party's basic line, policies and principles for
farmers, and also education on public and occupational morality
and family virtue. Rural education is the key to developing
agriculture through science, technology and education as a whole
and to improving the quality of rural population.
</P>
<P>
-- Intensify the building of grass-roots Party organization
and train a contingent of officials in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
The key to building a new socialist countryside with Chinese
characteristics lies in strengthening and improving Party
leadership, bringing into full play the leading role of
grass-roots Party organizations, and training qualified
grass-roots leading officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
