<HEADLINE> 11 Rebels killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka government troops
killed 11 Tamil rebels in Northern Province of the country
Saturday, according to a military spokesman here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the troops engaged a small group of Tamil
rebels with small arms, killing at least five terrorists Saturday
afternoon at Vannivi Lankulam in the Northern province.
</P>
<P>
