Mankulam, Government troops engaged a group of rebels with mortars
and small arms. Five Tamil rebels were killed and two others
injured in action.
</P>
<P>
Around 6:00 p.m. Saturday at Paranthan in Jaffna district,
troops sniped and killed one rebel, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a 15-year war against Sri
Lankan government for a separate state in the north and east of
the country. 
