<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 7-Party Alliance Calls for Hartal in Dhaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 18 (Xinhua) -- The 7-party alliance, led by the
main opposition, the Nationalist Party of Bangladesh (BNP), has
called a dawn-to-dusk hartal in Dhaka Sunday in protest against
what it said the government's "failures and misrule" in its
administration.
</P>
<P>
This is the first hartal in Dhaka after the ten-week-long
recent catastrophic floods, which hit 52 out of the country's 64
districts, affecting about half of the its 127 million people and
causing an estimated loss of about 4.3 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The day-long hartal is being organized in support of the
demands for interest-free loans for farmers, creation of
employment opportunities, opening of gruel kitchens in the
calamity zones, freeing of political prisoners and withdrawal of
fabricated cases filed against the opposition leaders and
activists, BNP sources claimed.
</P>
<P>
Vehicles used by hospitals, newspapers, law enforcing agencies,
water and power supply authorities, medicine shops and kitchen
markets would be exempted from the hartal, according to a BNP
press release issued Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
The government has deployed more than 4,000 police and
Bangladesh Rifles personnel in the city to maintain peace during
the hartal, media reports said.
</P>
<P>
To drum up support for today's hartal, the BNP brought out
torch processions at different places in the city Saturday
evening.
</P>
<P>
Police used batons and lobbed teargas shell after BNP activists
blasted crackers and ransacked vehicles in the city when they were
campaigning for hartal. In the police-BNP clashes occurred at some
places, some opposition workers were injured, and a policeman was
also hurt, reports said.
</P>
<P>
The hartal is going on, most of all the shops are closed and
very few pedestrians are seen in the streets.
</P>
<P>
Till now, there are no reports about clashes and arrests which
have occurred between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Formed last year, the 7-party alliance groups the BNP, the main
opposition in the country, the Jamaat-e-Islam Party, the
Bangladesh Jatiya Party, the Democratic League, the Jatiya
Gonatantrik Party, the National Democratic Alliance and the
Progressive Nationalist Party. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
