<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Maps Out Plan for Agricultural, Rural Development (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The decision also lists the main tasks for agricultural and
rural developments.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should be continued over a long period of time to
stabilize the system of combining unified and seperate operations
based on the household contract responsibility. The key
to this dual operation system is to stabilize and improve the land
contract. This is the cornerstone of the Party's rural policies
and the Party will never waver on this point. An effort must be
made to carry out the policy of extending the term of land
contracts for another 30 years.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should be made to deepen the reform of the circulation
system for farm produce and to improve the farm produce
markets. Grain is a strategic material and vitally important to
the growth of national economy and the improvement of people's
lives. So, the starting point for the reform of the grain
circulation system should be to guarantee a basic grain supply at
home, safeguard farmers' enthusiasm in grain production and
increase grain output.
</P>
<P>
Capital construction for agriculture should be accelerated and
the agro-ecosystem improved. Priority is to invest more in
harnessing large rivers and lakes including the Yangtze and Yellow
rivers to increase flood-control capacity.
</P>
<P>
Scientific and technological achievements must be used to
improve agricultural and rural economic structures. Revolution in
agro-science and technology must be promoted by applying the
achievements in bio-engineering and information industries on the
basis of the wide application of farm machinery, chemical
fertilizers, plastic sheeting and other industrial achivements.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981018.0146 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-18 </DATE_TIME>
