<HEADLINE> China Maps Out Plan for Agricultural, Rural Development (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Greater effort needs to be made to get a relatively
comfortable living standard in rural areas and to wipe out
poverty. Poverty relief spendings should be increased by a large
margin and should come from different sources. People living
in extremely adverse natural conditions should be resettled.
</P>
<P>
Grass-roots democracy and the legal system in rural areas
should be strngthened to promote democratic elections,
decision-making, management and supervision at the village level.
</P>
<P>
Socialist ethical and cultural progress should be strengthened
in rural areas, and farmers should be educated in patriotism,
collectivism, socialism, and the Party's basic line, guiding
principles and policies, as well as in public morality,
professional ethics and family virtues.
</P>
<P>
Grass-roots Party organizations and cadre groups in rural areas
should be improved. The key to building a new socialist
countryside with Chinese characteristics lies in strengthening and
improving the Party leadership, fully playing the part of
grass-roots Party organizations as the core of leadership, and in
building a high-quality contingent of grass-roots cadres.
</P>
<P>
The Third Plenum called on the entire Party and people of all
ethnic groups to hold high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping
Theory in creating a new situation in agriculture and rural work and
bringing into the 21st century the cause of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics under the CPC leadership with Jiang Zemin
at the core. 
