<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, October 18 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
Saturday urged Japan to take more steps to help improve world
economic growth by opening and deregulating its economy.
</P>
<P>
In a weekly radio address, Clinton said Japan, the world's
second-largest economy behind the United States, must open and
deregulate its economy to strengthen its financial system.
</P>
<P>
"Now it's critical to avoid further delay by moving quickly and
using that money most effectively ... Now the health of Asia's
economy -- and indeed the world -- depends upon Japan," he
said. (US-Japan-Economy)
</P>
<P>
- - - - - - -
</P>
<P>
BUCHAREST -- Romanian President Emil Constantinescu called
Saturday for addressing the very roots of poverty through the
country's economic development.
</P>
<P>
Social security system alone is not enough to tackle the
problem, Constantinescu said in announcing the beginning of
Romania's first national poverty alleviation
program. (Romania-Poverty Alleviation)
</P>
<P>
- - - - - - -
</P>
<P>
CARACAS -- The average price of Venezuelan crudes was down 0.92
U.S. dollar per barrel in the past week despite the start of
winter season in the northern hemisphere.
</P>
<P>
As winter comes, market demands often go up, but the crude
average went from 11.90 dollars per barrel last week to 10.98
dollars this week, said the Energy and Mines
Ministry. (Venezuela-Oil Price)
</P>
<P>
- - - - - - -
</P>
<P>
SAO PAULO -- Brazil's Petroleos Brasilenos (Petrobras) and
Argentina's Yacimientos Petroliferos Fiscales (YPF) will work
together on an oil project, industry sources said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The two state oil companies have signed an agreement to jointly
explore and exploit an oil field in the Brazilian state of
Espirito Santo.
</P>
<P>
The operation, to be kicked off before year 2000 in the oil
field known as BSE-3, some 116 kilometers (72 miles) northeast of
Vitoria city, is expected to cost 20 million
U.S. dollars. (Brazil-Argentina-Oil Project) 
