<DOCNO> XIE19981018.0151 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chileans Must Be Judged by Chilean Courts: President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Chileans should be tried by
Chilean courts, Chilean President Eduardo Frei said on Saturday
following the arrest of the country's former military chief
Augusto Pinochet in London.
</P>
<P>
Frei told Chilean reporters in Oporto, Portugal, that the
detention violated the diplomatic immunity Pinochet enjoys as
senator-for-life, and broke international law.
</P>
<P>
The 82-year-old former commander-in-chief of the Chilean army
was detained earlier Saturday at a London clinic where he had
received a minor surgery.
</P>
<P>
Frei said his country has lodged a formal protest to Britain
over the detention.
</P>
<P>
"We think that you have to respect Chilean laws. This condition
of diplomatic immunity protects all Chilean lawmakers ... People
in Chile must be judged by Chilean courts," said the president,
who is in Oporto for an Ibero-American summit.
</P>
<P>
British authorities said they were acting on a request from
Spanish courts probing Pinochet's role in alleged organized
killing of Spaniards in Chile during his rule of the country
between 1973 and 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
