<HEADLINE> Brazilian, Argentine Firms to Work Together on Oil Field </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAO PAULO, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's Petroleos Brasilenos
(Petrobras) and Argentina's Yacimientos Petroliferos Fiscales
(YPF) will work together on an oil project, industry sources said
here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The two state oil companies have signed an agreement to jointly
explore and exploit an oil field in the Brazilian state of
Espirito Santo.
</P>
<P>
