<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Maps Out Plan for Agricultural, Rural Development (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 18 (Xinhua) -- China made public today "the
Decision of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee
on Several Major Issues in Agriculture and Rural Work" adopted at
the Third Plenum of the 15th CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The decision, which consists of 10 parts with 18,000 Chinese
characters, summarizes the experiences in China's rural reform over
the past two decades and sets goals, guiding principles, tasks for
agriculture and rural work to the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
The Third Plenum of the 15th CPC Central Committee was held in
Beijing on October 12-14 to review the international and domestic
situation and agriculture and rural work. Those present concluded
that it was time for the Party to make decisions on some major
issues in agriculture and rural work.
</P>
<P>
The decision says China's primary stage of socialism is still
underdeveloped, especially in its rural areas, and the rural work
therefore must constantly focus on the development of rural
economy and the increase of agricultural production, with policies
conducive to vitalizing rural economy, changing the backward
conditions in rural areas, and improving the level of material and
cultural life of farmers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981018.0165 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Maps Out Plan for Agricultural, Rural Development (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Third Plenum set 3 major objectives for agricultural and
rural development from now to 2010:
</P>
<P>
First: economically, China should adhere to the public
ownership as the main form coupled with diverse forms of ownership
in order to emancipate and develop the productive forces;
</P>
<P>
Second: politically, China should adhere to the Party's
leadership, promote the development of socialist democratic
politics in rural areas, further expand grass-roots democracy, and
make certain that farmers directly exercise their democratic
rights in accordance with the law; and
</P>
<P>
Third: culturally, China should continue to promote socialist
ethical and cultural progress in rural areas to train new farmers
with lofty ideals, moral integrity, good education and good
discipline.
</P>
<P>
The plenum also provided 10 guiding principles for the
achievements of the trans-century goals for agricultural
and rural development:
</P>
<P>
-- Placing agriculture before everything else in national
economic development;
</P>
<P>
-- Stabilizing the fundamental economic system in rural areas
in which the major form of public ownership and diverse forms of
ownership develop simultaneously;
</P>
<P>
-- Continuing to grasp firmly grain production and develop a
diversified economy, so as to ensure the supply of farm produce
and steady increase of farmers' incomes;
</P>
<P>
-- Implementing the strategy of revitalizing agriculture
through science and technology;
</P>
<P>
-- Achieving a sustained agricultural growth;
</P>
<P>
-- Vigorously developing township-run enterprises to relocate
redundant rural laborers;
</P>
<P>
-- Taking practical measures to lighten farmers' burdens and
increase their incomes;
</P>
<P>
-- Carrying out the State policy of family planning;
</P>
<P>
-- Promoting the development of grass-roots democratic politics
in rural areas and safeguarding farmers' rights to make decisions
on their own affairs in accordance with the law; and
</P>
<P>
-- Paying equal attention to building material civilization and
ethical and cultural progress in rural areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
