<HEADLINE> CPV Plenum Urges to Push Up Renovation, Maintain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 17 (Xinhua)-- The Communist Party of Vietnam
(CPV) Saturday reaffirmed the country's determination to continue
with its renovation process, urged to overcome difficulties and
hardships and to maintain socio-economic stability.
</P>
<P>
This was made in a communique released at the end of the Sixth
Plenum (phase 1) of the CPV Central Committee which was held here
from October 13 to 17.
</P>
<P>
General Secretary Le Kha Phieu presided over the plenum and
delivered the opening and concluding speeches and Prime Minister
Phan Van Khai presented a report on the country's socio-economic
development.
</P>
<P>
The party central committee discussed the socio-economic
situation in 1998 and defined the orientation and tasks for
socio-economic development in 1999 and a number of issues vital to
agriculture and rural development, said the communique.
</P>
<P>
On the socio-economic situation of 1998, the plenum noted that
despite acute difficulties from severe natural calamities, the
financial and monetary crisis in the region and other countries in
the world, and a weak economy, the country achieved a growth rate
of six percent, and its social and political situation is stable.
</P>
<P>
The plenum also pointed out difficulties and weaknesses in the
country's socio-economic development.
</P>
<P>
With regard to the socio-economic plan for 1999, the plenum
said Vietnam "still faces severe and complicated challenges and
hardships due to the country's existing economic weaknesses, the
negative impacts of the regional economic crisis which may
continue, and the complicated and unprecedented occurrence of
natural calamities".
</P>
<P>
However, the communique said, Vietnam is enjoying "fundamental
advantages".
</P>
<P>
It said Vietnam's position and strength have been raised over
the past ten years of renovation.
</P>
<P>
The sixth plenum called on the entire people and party to bring
patriotism into full play, to thoroughly understand the country's
situations, to take part in labor emulation, to raise citizens'
responsibilities and sense of self-reliance, and to concentrate
all talents, wisdom, and material strength and finance to boost
production, and to build the country in the view of a prosperous
people, a strong country and a just and civilized society.
</P>
<P>
Sources here said the sixth plenum (phase 2) is to be held
later this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
