<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Attend Business Convention in Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 18 (Xinhua) -- An entrepreneurs delegation of
Myanmar will attend the Global Business Opportunity Convention
1998 in Osaka, Japan, scheduled to be held on Monday through to
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Aimed at promoting mutual cooperation in business enterprise
between entrepreneurs of Japan and Myanmar and exporting Myanmar
products to Japan, the 35-member Myanmar delegation will take part
in the convention, sponsored by the Osaka Chamber of Commerce and
Industry and its Myanmar counterpart.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar delegation comprises key members of the Union of
Myanmar Chamber of Commerce and Industry (UMCCI) and the Myanmar
Rice Millers Association.
</P>
<P>
The UMCCI, a major trade organization of its kind in Myanmar
out of 35, has signed 12 memorandums of understanding with its
counterparts from eight countries including four MOUs with Japan,
seeking economic cooperation with them.
</P>
<P>
The other MOUs were reached with those from Bangladesh,
Germany, Israel, South Korea, Nepal, Singapore and Thailand.
</P>
<P>
In February this year, chambers of commerce and industry of
Myanmar and Japan reached an agreement on the establishment of an
economic cooperation committee between the two sides to enhance
the economic cooperation of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, Japan had injected over 218.7
million U.S. dollars in 19 projects in Myanmar by the end of March
this year, ranking the ninth in 23 countries and regions which
invested over 7 billion dollars in the country. 
</P>
