<HEADLINE> Crude Oil Prices Down in Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The average price of Venezuelan
crudes was down 0.92 U.S. dollar per barrel in the past week
despite the start of winter season in the northern hemisphere.
</P>
<P>
As winter comes, market demands often go up, but the crude
average went from 11.90 dollars per barrel last week to 10.98
dollars this week, said the Energy and Mines Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Based on information available so far, the ministry projected
that the price this year would average 11.12 dollars per barrel.
</P>
<P>
The average oil price was 11.22 dollars in the first quarter of
this year, and 10.83 dollars in the third quarter. The average
price this month is estimated at 11.60 dollars per barrel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
