<HEADLINE> Sampras Enters Vienna Final to Meet Kucera </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, October 17 (Xinhua) -- World number one American Pete
Sampras beat fellow countryman Todd Martin 6-3, 7-6 (7-4) here on
Saturday to meet Slovak Karol Kucera at the CA-Trophy tennis
tournament final.
</P>
<P>
Kucera, ranked seventh in the world, upset Briton Greg
Rusedski 7-6 (8-6), 6-4 in the other semifinal.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, who is on his way to ending the year with his world
number one ranking for a record sixth consecutive year, appeared
exhausted in the second set after easily taking the first set
with a break in the fifth game.
</P>
<P>
Neither player had a break in the second set, which eventually
went into a tie-break won 7-4 by Sampras.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, 27, will probably have a hard time when he faces
Kucera on Sunday, battling for his fourth title this year.
</P>
<P>
Sampras has won three titles so far in 1998, including
Philadelphia, Atlanta and Wimbledon but was sent packing by
Kucera in the quarter-finals of the Australian Open this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
