<HEADLINE> Man United Narrow Villa's Lead to Four Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 17 (Xinhua) -- A 5-1 home victory over
Wimbledon helped Manchester United cut Aston Villa's lead at the
top of the English Premier League to four points on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
With Villa drawing 0-0 at West Ham United, United closed the
gap thanks to goals from Andy Cole (two), Ryan Giggs, David
Beckham and Dwight Yorke.
</P>
<P>
Villa have 21 points from nine games. United have 17 and have
played one game less.
</P>
<P>
Middlesbrough went third on 15 points after two late goals
gave them a 2-1 home win over Blackburn Rovers. Chelsea also
have 15 points after Gustavo Poyet's late winner secured a 2-1
home win over Charlton.
</P>
<P>
Champions Arsenal have 14 points after being held 1-1 at home
to bottom club Southampton. Newcastle United moved level with the
Gunners by beating Derby County 2-1 at St. James' Park.
</P>
<P>
The Merseyside derby between Everton and Liverpool finished
goalless at Goodison Park while Nottingham Forest were held 1-1
at home by managerless Leeds United. 
</P>
</TEXT>
